    "body": "lol at the 'Clonable types are copied with the clone method' tautology. I'm assuming I wrote that.\n\nThis characterization of clone as a deep copy vs. the shallow copies that the language itself makes kind of surprised me. `clone` originally just meant 'the copy operator for things that require copy constructors'. In the current landscape, where Rust won't do any deep copies, I can see how you would want to frame `clone` as being for deep copies, but I wonder if that's an oversimplification.\n",
